Mymensingh Zilla School is one of the renowned schools in [[Bangladesh]] which was established in [[1853]]. This school is mainly boy's school and it has two shifts(morning and day). The morning shift starts at 7.30 am and day shifts starts at 12.00 noon. Though it is a boy's school, it has both male and female teachers. This school has one headmaster but it has separate teachers for morning and day shifts. This school has a big playground, a big pond, three large buildings, one hall room and one [[dormitory]]. A mosque is also located next to the playground where most of the Muslim students and teachers take their prayers. This school has the facility for study from third grade to tenth grade. Every year student are admitted in third grade and sixth grade of this school. Moreover, in each grade, there are two sections, Section A and Section B. It is one of the oldest school which has the highest quality of education in the supervision of highly experienced and skilled teachers. Besides, the academic fee of this government school is quite low.

